Task: Fix generate_gdlintrc() to YAML set format

Summary:
Changed generate_gdlintrc() in config.py to output YAML !!set format
instead of plain text. The function now uses yaml.dump() to serialize
the exclude list as a YAML set with the 'excluded_directories' key,
matching the format gdtoolkit expects.

Files modified:
- src/gd_tools/config.py: Added 'import yaml', changed generate_gdlintrc()
  to use yaml.dump() with set() for the exclude list
- tests/unit/test_config.py: Added 5 tests for YAML set format validation
  (format, entries, parseability, config matching, custom excludes)

Why:
gdtoolkit expects gdlintrc files in YAML set format
(excluded_directories: !!set { dir: null, ... }), not plain text.
The previous implementation wrote one path per line, which gdtoolkit
could not parse correctly.
